doc.ContractDescription: THERE ARE TWO PRIMARY OBJECTIVES FOR THIS INVESTIGATION. FIRST, WE PROPOSE TO LAUNCH A PREEXISTING PAYLOAD TO CONTINUE OUR CURRENT PROGRAM OF SCIENTIFIC INVESTIGATIONS. SECOND, WE PROPOSE TO BUILD A NEW PAYLOAD WHICH WILL INTEGRATE AND DEMONSTRATE KEY TECHNOLOGIES VITAL TO FUTURE X-RAY OBSERVATORIES. THESE EFFORTS WILL TRAIN GRADUATE STUDENTS AND PREPARE JUNIOR RESEARCHERS TO BE MAJOR CONTRIBUTORS TO THE NEXT SUITE OF NASA MISSIONS. THE DISCOVERIES OF CHANDRA AND XMM HAVE SOLIDIFIED THE IMPORTANCE OF HIGH RESOLUTION SPECTROSCOPY, ESPECIALLY IN THE SOFT X-RAY BAND. HOWEVER, MISSION END DATES FOR THESE OBSERVATORIES ARE ON THE HORIZON, WHILE NEW OBSERVATORIES ARE BEING PLANNED. NEARLY ALL OF THE XRAY EMISSION AND ABSORPTION LINES FOR ASTROPHYSICALLY ABUNDANT ELEMENTS EXIST AT ENERGIES BELOW 2 KEV. RESOLUTIONS (λ/Δλ) OF SEVERAL HUNDRED ARE REQUIRED TO RESOLVE IMPORTANT DIAGNOSTIC LINES SUCH AS THE HE-LIKE TRIPLETS OF ABUNDANT ELEMENTS WHILE RESOLUTIONS OF THOUSANDS ARE REQUIRED FOR ACCURATE LINE PROFILES AND FINE VELOCITY RESOLUTION. MANY FUTURE MISSIONS AND OBSERVATORIES PLAN TO USE X-RAY MICROCALORIMETERS AS THE INSTRUMENT OF CHOICE FOR SPECTROSCOPY. HOWEVER, THESE INSTRUMENTS HAVE FINITE ENERGY RESOLUTION THAT STRUGGLES TO GO BELOWδE ~ 2 EV. FOR THIS REASON, WE PROPOSE TO INCREASE THE TECHNICAL READINESS OF GRATINGS TO OBTAIN HIGH RESOLUTION AT ENERGIES BELOW 1 KEV. THE CONCEPT THAT WILL BE DEVELOPED IN THIS PROPOSED INVESTIGATION WILL BE CAPABLE OF MEETING THE REQUIREMENTS OF FUTURE X-RAY OBSERVATORIES. IN ADDITION, THE DESIGN COULD BE UTILIZED EFFECTIVELY ON SMALLER, EXPLORER CLASS MISSIONS AS PATHFINDERS TO THE LARGER OBSERVATORIES WHILE PROVIDING IMPORTANT SCIENTIFIC INSIGHTS ALONG THE WAY.

doc.ContractDescription: THE NEXT FACILITY-CLASS X-RAY ASTRONOMY OBSERVATORY WILL BE ESA'S ATHENA MISSION, TO BE LAUNCHED IN 2028. ONE OF THE CORE ATHENA INSTRUMENTS, THE WIDE FIELD IMAGER (WFI), IS DESIGNED TO CONDUCT SENSITIVE OBSERVATIONS OF BOTH BRIGHT AND FAINT X-RAY SOURCES USING A WIDE FIELD OF VIEW AND A NEW TYPE OF DEVICE KNOWN AS A DEPFET (DEPLETED P-CHANNEL FIELD EFFECT TRANSISTOR) DETECTOR. WE PROPOSE TO PROVIDE A US CONTRIBUTION TO THE WFI INSTRUMENT, CONSISTING OF HARDWARE AND SOFTWARE DESIGNED TO PERFORM ON-BOARD HIGH-LEVEL ANALYSIS OF THE SCIENCE DATA STREAM, PLUS ASIC DESIGN AND TESTING EFFORTS. IN THIS PROPOSAL WE SEEK FUNDS TO DEVELOP THESE CONTRIBUTIONS THROUGH FY2019, IN SUPPORT OF THE WFI TEAM'S DESIGN EFFORTS LEADING TO MISSION ADOPTION AT ESA (CY2020).
